This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as it proposes a methodology for generating realistic flow-based network traffic for evaluating network-based intrusion detection systems. Additionally, it may also belong to the sub-category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it deals with flow-based data sets and network traffic. The use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) also suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions the use of quality tests which could involve image processing techniques, indicating that it may also belong to the sub-category of Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV).
